President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump hosted the 139th Easter Egg Roll at the White House. The President thanked everyone for attending and mentioned that the Easter Egg Roll has been a tradition since 1878. The President, along with Melania and their son Barron, planned to sign cards for soldiers before joining the attendees for the event. Melania also spoke, expressing her gratitude to the military and wishing everyone a happy Easter. The President concluded by wishing everyone a great time and joining the festivities.